<subSubSection id="8BE365737706EA77FF58DE71FB0EFC6B" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" type="description">
<paragraph id="C34636F87706EA77FF58DE71FEA8FCB3" blockId="1.[151,1436,564,1200]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="F18DEAEA7706EA77FF58DE71FEB3FDFE" bold="true" box="[151,324,564,589]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Redescription.</emphasis>
Body small-sized, slender or stubby. Head not exserted or slightly exserted above upper level of pronotum; vertex generally narrower than or as broad as or wider than an eye, vertex distinctly concave between eyes; in profile, vertex and frontal costa forming a round or obtuse shape, frontal costa before eyes not visible sometimes. Frontal costa bifurcate behind the paired ocelli, fontal costa protruding as arch between antennae, paired ocelli placed between the middle of the eyes. Antennae filiform, inserted below lower margins of eyes. Eyes globular in shape.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C34636F87706EA77FF08DF48FB0EFC6B" blockId="1.[151,1436,564,1200]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Pronotum truncate anteriorly, midkeel of pronotum entire, lateral keels of prozona distinct. Humeral apex ridge and lower margin of pronotum connected in the middle or behind middle of lower margin of pronotum. Posterior angles of lateral lobes of pronotum produced outwards, end of posterior angles truncate, posterior margin of each lateral lobe with two bisinuates. Tegmina normal. Wings not reaching or reaching or surpassing the caudal end of pronotum. Fore and middle femora elongated, margins straight or undulated; hind femora stubby, outer and inner side of hind tibia with distinct spines, first and third posterior tarsal segments nearly equal in length.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8BE365737706EA77FF08DFA1FD04FB03" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C34636F87706EA77FF08DFA1FD04FB03" blockId="1.[151,1436,564,1200]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="F18DEAEA7706EA77FF08DFA1FE3AFC4E" bold="true" box="[199,461,996,1021]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus is similar to 
<emphasis id="F18DEAEA7706EA77FD13DFA1FCABFC4F" box="[732,860,996,1020]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Bolivarittix</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A7684B097706EA77FCADDFA1FBF2FC4F" author="Gunther" box="[866,1029,996,1021]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" refString="Gunther, K. (1939) Revision der Acrydiinae (Orthoptera), III. Sectio Amorphopi (Metrodorae Bol. 1887 auct.). Abhandlungen und Berichte der Museum fur Tierkunde und Volkerkunde zu Dresden, (A), 20, 1 - 335." type="journal article" year="1939">G端nther, 1939</bibRefCitation>
, but differs from humeral apex ridge and lower margin of pronotum connected in the middle or behind middle of lower margin of pronotum (humeral apex ridge and lower margin of pronotum connected before middle of lower margin of pronotum in 
<emphasis id="F18DEAEA7706EA77FAD3D869FA6CFBF7" box="[1308,1435,1068,1092]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Bolivarittix</emphasis>
G端nther). It appears similar also to 
<taxonomicName id="04F94D7B7706EA77FDE0D815FBBFFBDB" authority="Zheng, Wei &amp; Jiang, 2005" authorityName="Zheng, Wei &amp; Jiang" authorityYear="2005" box="[559,1096,1103,1128]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettixoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F18DEAEA7706EA77FDE0D815FCF9FBDB" box="[559,782,1104,1128]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Macromotettixoides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A7684B097706EA77FCD8D80AFBBFFBDB" author="Zheng" box="[791,1096,1103,1128]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" refString="Zheng, Z. M., Wei, Z. M. &amp; Jiang, G. F. (2005) A neW genus and a neW species of Metrodoridae (Orthoptera) from China. Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 30 (2), 366 - 367." type="journal article" year="2005">Zheng, Wei &amp; Jiang, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter by posterior margin of each lateral lobe of pronotum with two bisinuates (posterior margin of each lateral lobe of pronotum with one concavity in 
<taxonomicName id="04F94D7B7706EA77FDCBD8DDFD14FB03" authorityName="Zheng, Wei &amp; Jiang" authorityYear="2005" box="[516,739,1176,1200]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Macromotettixoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F18DEAEA7706EA77FDCBD8DDFD14FB03" box="[516,739,1176,1200]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Macromotettixoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
